commitResults.messageBody: Updated UserGuide with deleteClient to satisfy tP requirement.
Updated the command string required for delete to deleteClient
Person classes and attributes within methods were refactored to Client in order to keep in theme with our tP.

Originally, there was a NullPointerException that was triggered in the UiManager class.

Identified the bug within ClientListPanel due to a capital error mistake. Hence, this update is to patch the bug.
Corrected a mispelling within LogicManagerTest from 'Person' to 'Client'

Implemented an autosort feature whereby the procedures will get autosort by date when a client adds them.

In essence, the newly added Procedures will be sorted by LocalDate (in ascending order), in which the more urgent ones will be placed on top.

In the previous PR, the comparison between the two Date classes for the autosort feature was between LocalDate.

However, in a later update to master, we have updated the Date class to use LocalDateTime instead. Hence, this PR is to update the autosort feature to reflect that.

This PR also updated the compareTo to compare the Date class with another Date object as commented by @iztanpy.
As per tP requirements, this PR's goal is to add Alexander's portion to the DG. This commit adds the Sequence Diagram for AddProcCommand.

Updated DG as per tP specifications.

This is a second part commit to build upon the previous one. The sequence diagram has been corrected and the main DG itself has addProc command reflected in it.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update UG as per tP requirements
commitResults.messageBody: This is a partial update to the UG to match our current progress. Some examples include updating the mock-up GUI to proper screenshots of our app.

Added (pseudo) randomly generated tests. These tests will take three random procedures and attempt to sort them via addProcCommand's method. Then, it will compare this new Procedure list with an expected, previously sorted one.
Fixed poor usage of magic numbers. Added in two leap years in date generator for variety. Added in Javadoc in a method in addProcCommand.
The old link was mapped to AB3 user guide. This PR updates it to map to our team's user guide instead.
